stylometry:
Decision trees are important in problem solving because they provide the decision maker with a view of all of the important aspects of a problem at one time. This is useful in its own right due to the insight it provides. Decision trees provide the framework for doing EMV calculations. Decision trees also allow us to use the folding back approach to calculate EMVs and the optimal decision.

Decision trees can be used in many different ways. One example is deciding on marketing nationally or having a test market first. You can see the probability of how well a test market will do, and then decide whether or not marketing nationally would be a good idea.
